@node 1 " BBS_LiST GUiDE v2 [c]1997 Glen Martin    [Page 1 of 6] "
@prev main
@next 2



                   @{"            Description!            " link 1}

 In brief, BBS_LiST is simply a MAXs Door that displays the Oz BBS Listings.
 Also allows you to download the Oz BBS Listings archive.

 This MAXs Door is only suitable for Ozzie MAXs SysOps ...

 This is a slightly updated version from the original, nutting special and
 only some minor changes and additions, etc. Lump it or like it!

@endnode
@node 2 " BBS_LiST GUiDE v2 [c]1997 Glen Martin    [Page 2 of 6] "
@prev 1
@next 3



                   @{"            Installation            " link 2}

 Very simple indeed, Unpack the BBS_LiST archive into your Doors directory.

@endnode
@node 3 " BBS_LiST GUiDE v2 [c]1997 Glen Martin    [Page 3 of 6] "
@prev 2
@next 4



                   @{"            Instructions            " link 3}

 Grab the latest/current copy of the Australian BBS Listings archive. The
 copy of lists included are from Sept96 (BBS9609.LZH). In the archive you
 are too use the archive BBSDALL.LZH. With each new version of the Listings
 you are to unpack the #?.TXT files from BBSDALL.LZH into the directory
 called LiSTS within the directory BBS_LiST. Also place the copy of
 BBSDALL.LZH in the LiSTS dir, as well. In the LiSTS dir there should be a
 total of 10 files; 9 #?.TXT files, and the BBSDALL.LZH archive.

 The Door to run in MAXs (Function 34) is BBS_LiST.exe, and the menu to be
 displayed is called BBS_LiST.menu. Both these files reside in the main dir
 called BBS_LiST. The file BBS_LiST.heading is shown before the BBS lists.
 Just set it all up as it is, when you unpack it into your Doors dir ...

@endnode
